webpackJsonp([0x79097a60c108],{1015:function(a,e){a.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"Justin Ball",author:"Justin Ball"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/jbasdf/projects/justinball/src/posts/2008-03-19-big-companies-using-ruby-on-rails/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>I am frequently asked how reliable/scalable is Ruby on Rails? I usually tell people about <a href="http://twitter.com//">Twitter</a>or more recently point them to <a href="http://highscalability.com/friends-sale-architecture-300-million-page-view-month-facebook-ror-app">this article about the Friend\'s For Sale Facebook application</a>. The answer is, yes Rails scales just fine. The trick is getting your database to scale.</p>\n<p>Anyway, <a href="http://blog.obiefernandez.com/content/2008/03/big-name-compan.html">Obie Fernandez, a major name in the Rails community put together a list of the big companies that are using Rails</a>.</p>\n<p>Here are two of the places to look for the big Rails deployments:\n<a href="http://rails100.pbwiki.com/">http://rails100.pbwiki.com/</a>\n<a href="http://www.workingwithrails.com/high-profile-organisations">http://www.workingwithrails.com/high-profile-organisations</a>.</p>\n<p>The elegant, framework that lets developers enjoy their job once again is scalable and will work for you application. I love Ruby on Rails.</p>',frontmatter:{title:"Big Companies Using Ruby on Rails",date:"March 19, 2008",imageUrl:null,image:null}}},pathContext:{path:"/big-companies-using-ruby-on-rails"}}}});
